WEBVTT

00:00.967 --> 00:04.471
[ music ]

00:08.842 --> 00:10.610
[ On TV] JACOB'S FATHER:
Jacob, I told you to put

00:10.677 --> 00:12.112
that kie-oat down!

00:12.178 --> 00:15.081
JACOB: I did, Pa!
But he rose up from his grave!

00:15.148 --> 00:17.150
And now he's a...
zombie coyote!

00:17.217 --> 00:19.452
[ zombie coyote howls ]

00:19.519 --> 00:21.855
[ laughs ]

00:21.921 --> 00:23.456
[ chainsaw revving ]

00:23.523 --> 00:26.493
JACOB: How did he pick up
and operate that chainsaw?!

00:26.559 --> 00:27.927
- Oh my god!

00:27.994 --> 00:29.562
JACOB: Oh no!

00:31.264 --> 00:33.433
- What's your problem, man?
- Hmm?

00:33.500 --> 00:35.468
- What's your problem, man?

00:35.535 --> 00:37.804
- Nothin'.
It's just a funny movie.

00:37.871 --> 00:39.339
- It's not a funny movie!
- I wet my pants.

00:39.406 --> 00:40.840
- It's a scary movie!
- Terrifying!

00:40.907 --> 00:42.542
- It's a movie about
zombie coyotes.

00:42.609 --> 00:46.646
- Whoa, whoa. I'm getting a lot
of negativity in my direction.

00:46.713 --> 00:49.716
Reminds me of the time that
I said I didn't like Fortnite.

00:49.783 --> 00:50.884
- You're bad at it.

00:50.950 --> 00:52.385
- A hundred billion
subscribers.

00:52.452 --> 00:54.387
That's billion. With a "B."

00:54.454 --> 00:57.891
- Alright, that's enough,
that's enough, that's enough.

00:57.957 --> 01:00.693
Now, can we please turn
the movie on

01:00.760 --> 01:04.831
so I can laugh and enjoy
my Bro-maha Steaks.

01:04.897 --> 01:06.566
- That's another thing!
- Yeah!

01:06.633 --> 01:08.001
- Oh, god...

01:08.067 --> 01:09.702
- Not only are you laughing
at our scary movie,

01:09.769 --> 01:11.237
you're sittin' here eatin'
Bromaha Steaks

01:11.304 --> 01:12.672
right in our faces.
- Yeah.

01:12.739 --> 01:14.407
And all we have is candy,
and popcorn, and sodas,

01:14.474 --> 01:16.309
and donuts, and taffy,
and slushies.

01:16.376 --> 01:18.678
I mean what the heck, man?

01:18.745 --> 01:22.415
- Okay first of all,
I bought these steaks myself

01:22.482 --> 01:26.152
with my own dad's credit card.

01:26.219 --> 01:30.323
And second of all,
I don't get scared.

01:30.390 --> 01:31.724
- Yes you do.
- Yes you do!

01:31.791 --> 01:33.593
- Yeah you get scared
all the time

01:33.660 --> 01:35.562
and you do your tiny shriek.
- Yeah, it's like, "Oh huh!"

01:35.628 --> 01:37.564
- No, no, no, it's more
high-pitched. It's like, "AHH!"

01:37.630 --> 01:38.932
- No, no, no, you gotta go
even higher than that,

01:38.998 --> 01:39.933
[ higher pitched AHH! ]

01:39.999 --> 01:41.267
- No no no no no no no no...

01:41.334 --> 01:46.039
[ all imitating Henry's shriek ]

01:46.105 --> 01:48.107
- No, I only do that
when I'm startled, okay?

01:48.174 --> 01:49.509
Not when I'm scared.

01:49.576 --> 01:52.178
- Startled? Yeah?
Startled, my foot!

01:52.245 --> 01:54.414
- Well I'm sorry, okay?

01:54.481 --> 01:57.283
I just don't get scared.
Alright?

01:57.350 --> 01:58.852
Just calm down, buddy?

02:00.787 --> 02:01.621
- Challenge.

02:01.688 --> 02:03.456
- Ooooooh!
- Ohhhhh!

02:03.523 --> 02:06.292
- Dance battle!
- No, no...

02:06.359 --> 02:07.961
I already beat Henry
in a dance battle.

02:08.026 --> 02:09.529
- You did.
I got served.

02:09.596 --> 02:11.397
I'm big enough to admit it.
- For this challenge...

02:11.464 --> 02:14.133
I'm going to scare you.

02:14.200 --> 02:16.269
- Can't be done.

02:16.336 --> 02:17.804
- Oh yes it can.

02:17.871 --> 02:21.608
I'm gonna tell you a story
so scary it'll...

02:21.674 --> 02:26.913
scare you.
- Bring it.

02:26.980 --> 02:28.815
- And if I do scare you,

02:28.882 --> 02:32.452
we get... your whole box
of Bro-maha Steaks!

02:32.519 --> 02:33.820
- Oh? Oh you want
my Bro-maha steaks?

02:33.887 --> 02:36.322
You want my steaks?
You want these steaks?

02:36.389 --> 02:37.390
Well look at these guys
over here.

02:37.457 --> 02:38.791
- Man in the pink shirt.

02:38.858 --> 02:40.660
- Alright. Oh don't come
for my pink shirt, dude.

02:40.727 --> 02:43.129
I can't be scared, okay,
you 'Fraidy Gagas!

02:43.196 --> 02:44.497
- Oh yeah! So we got a bet?

02:44.564 --> 02:46.966
- Yeah we got a bet.
You bet we got a bet.

02:47.033 --> 02:48.401
Let's hear your story.

02:48.468 --> 02:49.802
- Oh you're not just
gonna hear my story.

02:49.869 --> 02:53.339
You're gonna see my story.
In your brain.

02:53.406 --> 02:55.575
[ Schwoz giggles ]

02:55.642 --> 02:57.310
- What?

02:58.578 --> 03:02.248
- Schwoz?
Get the Story Tank.

03:05.318 --> 03:07.587
- Beep.
- I don't like that.

03:11.758 --> 03:14.928
{\an5}- and the sensory suit will
also measure
the "fearitol" levels

03:14.994 --> 03:18.031
in Henry's body.
- Fearitol?

03:18.097 --> 03:20.266
What is that, some chemical
that your body produces

03:20.333 --> 03:21.868
when you're scared?
- Yes!

03:21.935 --> 03:25.305
- Well you better make sure
that monitor can read zero,

03:25.371 --> 03:28.942
because that's how much
fearitol my body produces.

03:29.008 --> 03:32.545
- Uh, yeah.
- I said well--

03:32.612 --> 03:34.948
- We heard you.
- Wow. Love you, friends.

03:35.014 --> 03:38.017
- Be quiet we're trying to divvy
up the steaks we're gonna win!

03:38.084 --> 03:39.452
- Aw, that's cute...

03:39.519 --> 03:42.055
you actually think
you can scare me.

03:42.121 --> 03:43.856
By telling me a story.

03:43.923 --> 03:46.359
- Oh, Henry...

03:46.426 --> 03:50.330
poor, simple Henry...

03:50.396 --> 03:53.566
I'm not just going to tell you
a story.

03:53.633 --> 03:55.568
I'm going to make you
live the story.

03:57.136 --> 03:59.906
- I'm already not caring about
what you are saying.

03:59.973 --> 04:01.774
- Maybe you'll care now!

04:04.043 --> 04:06.312
[ laughter ]

04:14.554 --> 04:16.522
- So...
where am I?

04:16.589 --> 04:20.360
- You're in the Story Zone,
deep inside your brain.

04:20.426 --> 04:22.829
RAY: When I tell my story,
you'll experience it

04:22.895 --> 04:25.932
in the Story Zone as though
it's really happening to you.

04:25.999 --> 04:30.436
For instance, if I say that
you're standing near a camel

04:30.503 --> 04:32.972
made of chocolate...

04:36.309 --> 04:38.111
- Okay, that's pretty sweet.

04:38.177 --> 04:40.847
RAY: Is it? I don't think
you'll find it sweet

04:40.913 --> 04:43.783
when you realize that
my scary story starts off...

04:43.850 --> 04:46.986
outside of a house
very much like your own house.

04:49.956 --> 04:51.124
- Okay.

04:51.190 --> 04:52.759
RAY: But the difference is...

04:52.825 --> 04:57.230
this house...
is haunted.

04:57.296 --> 04:59.465
[ Ray makes
door creaking sound ]

04:59.532 --> 05:02.435
{\an5}- I can tell that's just you
making the door sound
with your mouth.

05:04.604 --> 05:07.840
[ high pitched ]
- No it's not.

05:14.147 --> 05:15.214
- It all just kinda happened.

05:15.281 --> 05:16.582
I wanted an after-school job.

05:16.649 --> 05:18.584
But then,
an indestructible superhero

05:18.651 --> 05:20.887
hired me to be his sidekick.
- Ah!

05:20.953 --> 05:23.122
- Now we blow bubbles...
and fight crime.

05:23.189 --> 05:25.058
Feels good.

05:25.124 --> 05:30.496
[ theme music ]

05:38.304 --> 05:41.174
- Call it.
- Up the tube!

05:41.240 --> 05:43.576
- Aw, my boot!
- Ha!

05:46.245 --> 05:48.648
[ music ]

05:48.715 --> 05:52.151
- So, Henry... how does it feel
to stand outside a...

05:52.218 --> 05:53.920
haunted house?

05:53.986 --> 05:56.255
- I'll tell you how it
doesn't feel -- scary.

05:56.322 --> 05:57.623
So you guys
should just give up now

05:57.690 --> 06:00.193
'cuz you're not
getting my steaks.

06:00.259 --> 06:01.794
- Is he scared at all?

06:01.861 --> 06:04.630
- No, his fearitol level
is at one-hundred.

06:04.697 --> 06:07.266
Which is like zero
in fearitol levels.

06:07.333 --> 06:08.935
- Then why not
just make it zero?

06:09.001 --> 06:11.704
- Hey guys! My bore-it-all
levels are off the charts

06:11.771 --> 06:14.040
so can we please
get on with the story?

06:14.107 --> 06:17.677
- Yes. So you're about to enter
a haunted house.

06:17.744 --> 06:19.312
RAY: But you're not alone.

06:19.378 --> 06:21.981
- What, is there like a ghost
in the doorway or something?

06:22.048 --> 06:24.550
- Ooooooooooo!

06:24.617 --> 06:27.854
RAY: No, no! There's no ghost
in the doorway.

06:27.920 --> 06:29.922
- Ooooooooooo...

06:31.457 --> 06:32.992
- Nice try, buddy.

06:33.059 --> 06:35.294
- But there is
someone else there.

06:35.361 --> 06:37.029
A friend.

06:37.096 --> 06:39.999
RAY: A handsome friend
with huge muscles.

06:40.066 --> 06:42.468
RAY: And eyes that smolder
like a sunset.

06:42.535 --> 06:44.537
And hair like a waterfall but--

06:44.604 --> 06:47.039
[ groans ] - Can we please just
get on with the story?

06:47.106 --> 06:48.908
RAY: Sure.

06:48.975 --> 06:49.909
- Follow me.

06:49.976 --> 06:53.579
If you dare...
- I dare.

06:53.646 --> 06:55.114
- Wait no you're supposed to
follow me!

06:57.049 --> 06:58.184
- Looks like my house.

06:58.251 --> 07:00.019
- Only...
spookier.

07:00.086 --> 07:01.721
- Same couch though, so...

07:01.788 --> 07:03.356
- Yeah well this couch is kinda
big, it's kinda hard to move--

07:03.422 --> 07:04.590
- Yeah well I'm just saying,
if the couch was different

07:04.657 --> 07:05.825
it might be scarier.

07:05.892 --> 07:07.026
- The story's not about
the couch!

07:07.093 --> 07:08.027
- Well it could be. So.

07:08.094 --> 07:11.264
- Greetings!

07:11.330 --> 07:15.334
- Where'd he come from?

07:15.401 --> 07:16.602
- The kitchen?

07:16.669 --> 07:18.271
- I'm leaving for the winter

07:18.337 --> 07:20.506
and I need a caretaker
for this house.

07:20.573 --> 07:22.008
- We'll do it.

07:22.074 --> 07:24.443
Caretaking your house
will give me time to write.

07:24.510 --> 07:27.346
I'm a writer.
- Gross.

07:27.413 --> 07:28.748
- What are you writing?

07:28.815 --> 07:30.183
- It's gonna take me all winter

07:30.249 --> 07:33.386
but I'm going to write
the Great American Meme.

07:33.452 --> 07:34.787
- What?
- Oooh...

07:34.854 --> 07:36.556
- It's gonna be based on
a stock photograph

07:36.622 --> 07:38.457
and it's gonna have
a hilarious caption

07:38.524 --> 07:40.593
and capture
the voice of our times.

07:40.660 --> 07:43.296
- I love captions.
- That's what memes do.

07:43.362 --> 07:44.630
- Best of luck to you.

07:44.697 --> 07:50.303
But before I go,
you should know one thing.

07:50.369 --> 07:51.737
- Where the bathrooms are?

07:51.804 --> 07:56.275
- No. Well, yes.
But you should also know

07:56.342 --> 08:02.114
that the last caretaker
of this house went crazy.

08:06.452 --> 08:07.987
- Ah. I get it.

08:08.054 --> 08:09.722
Ray's gonna go crazy.
- Maybe I will...

08:09.789 --> 08:13.659
- Well I know you will because
what else would happen--

08:13.726 --> 08:16.762
- Well I hope
he doesn't go crazy.

08:16.829 --> 08:19.498
Because the last caretaker
of this house

08:19.565 --> 08:23.803
sewed his daughters' clothes
together.

08:23.870 --> 08:28.174
Now those clothes
will be together forever...

08:28.241 --> 08:32.178
and ever...
and...

08:32.245 --> 08:37.582
Oopsie.
...and ever...and ever.

08:38.818 --> 08:40.753
[ Ray makes
door creaking sound ]

08:44.991 --> 08:46.926
- Why don't you go upstairs
and unpack?

08:46.993 --> 08:51.163
While I stay down here,
not going crazy.

08:53.566 --> 08:55.601
- Unpack what?
I don't have any bags.

08:55.668 --> 08:57.036
- Oh really?

08:57.103 --> 08:59.705
[ Ray makes
door creaking sound ]

09:01.607 --> 09:03.109
- Nice.
- Yeah.

09:03.175 --> 09:07.813
- But too bad for you
I'm not scared of suitcases.

09:07.880 --> 09:10.883
- Just go upstairs okay!
- Fine.

09:10.950 --> 09:13.019
- But be careful.
You never know

09:13.085 --> 09:15.488
what you might find
at the top of the...

09:15.554 --> 09:17.757
scares.

09:21.260 --> 09:23.896
I said... you never know
what you might find

09:23.963 --> 09:29.001
at the top of the--
- I heard you!

09:29.068 --> 09:30.636
- Scares.

09:35.107 --> 09:36.242
- Hello Henry.

09:36.309 --> 09:37.743
- Ahhh!

09:37.810 --> 09:39.745
CHARLOTTE: Ahh!
- We scared him!

09:39.812 --> 09:41.180
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

09:41.247 --> 09:45.017
♪ I want something else
to get me through this ♪

09:45.084 --> 09:47.553
♪ Semi-charmed kind of life ♪

09:47.620 --> 09:49.488
- No no no no no
I was startled, not scared!

09:49.555 --> 09:51.090
Check my fearitol level!

09:51.157 --> 09:52.091
- Oh! He was startled!

09:52.158 --> 09:55.494
- I was.
Just check it, Schwoz.

09:55.561 --> 09:57.029
- Was he scared?

09:57.096 --> 10:00.266
- He was almost
scared two seconds ago...

10:00.333 --> 10:03.269
no, he was never fully
in the scare zone!

10:03.336 --> 10:05.071
- Ah!
- Why?

10:05.137 --> 10:06.605
- What?

10:06.672 --> 10:09.108
- Also real quick, big dog.
Is that your celebration music?

10:09.175 --> 10:10.276
- Yeah. Third Eye Blind.

10:10.343 --> 10:12.078
Semi-Charmed Life.
Why?

10:12.144 --> 10:14.080
- Just random.

10:14.146 --> 10:15.581
- It's not random.
It's awesome.

10:15.648 --> 10:17.249
- It's a little random.
- Best song...

10:17.316 --> 10:18.884
- My mom loves that song.

10:18.951 --> 10:20.419
- I don't know what it's about,
but it's awesome.

10:20.486 --> 10:22.355
PIPER: Ray, you are old.

10:22.421 --> 10:25.024
{\an5}- Just flip your visor down
and make sure
you're wearing pants.

10:25.091 --> 10:26.559
- I think you know
I'm wearing pants.

10:26.625 --> 10:27.960
- Good.
- Great.

10:28.027 --> 10:30.296
- Cuz I'm about to scare 'em
off. Flip!

10:30.363 --> 10:32.131
- Flipping.

10:32.198 --> 10:35.868
- Okay, you're in your room,
unpacking with the scary twins

10:35.935 --> 10:37.770
whose clothes
have been sewn together...

10:37.837 --> 10:41.707
- Okay, socks go in the drawer.
Sweater in the closet.

10:50.883 --> 10:53.753
- Downstairs, the author
is having trouble

10:53.819 --> 10:57.690
coming up with ideas
for the Great American Meme.

11:02.795 --> 11:05.097
Gah! I can't think of
any good memes.

11:05.164 --> 11:08.901
SCHWOZ:
How about something with cats?

11:08.968 --> 11:11.637
- What are you doing?
- Oh I'm just...

11:11.704 --> 11:14.874
"The Shining" this glass.

11:16.342 --> 11:18.944
- Yeah well references
to old movies

11:19.011 --> 11:22.181
aren't gonna help me write
the Great American Meme.

11:22.248 --> 11:26.485
- You could try taking an axe
and smashing the door

11:26.552 --> 11:30.756
to Henry's bedroom
and hurting him.

11:34.026 --> 11:36.262
- I don't know
if I should hurt Henry.

11:36.328 --> 11:41.600
- C'moooonnnn.
- Okay I'll hurt him.

11:41.667 --> 11:44.770
You got an axe?
- I got this.

11:46.205 --> 11:48.274
- Good enough.

11:53.279 --> 11:54.947
Hey wait a second.

11:55.014 --> 11:57.883
I thought we were
alone in this house.

12:02.388 --> 12:08.360
Oh boy I really have
gone crazy...

12:12.698 --> 12:16.335
- Come play with us, Henry.
- Sure.

12:16.402 --> 12:20.239
As long as it's not Fortnite,
I'm in.

12:20.306 --> 12:24.844
Little pigs, little pigs,
let me come in.

12:24.910 --> 12:26.745
- Okay, come on in.

12:28.147 --> 12:29.849
- Are...
- Door's unlocked.

12:29.915 --> 12:31.584
- You...
- Just turn the handle, dude.

12:31.650 --> 12:34.987
- Scared...Yet?

12:37.490 --> 12:38.924
- No. I'm not.

12:38.991 --> 12:40.192
- Are you for real?
- Are you serious?

12:40.259 --> 12:41.360
- Well, I'm sorry.

12:41.427 --> 12:44.096
- Well... what
if the ghost came back?!

12:44.163 --> 12:49.034
RAY: Would you be scared then?

12:49.101 --> 12:51.270
The owner of the house is back!

12:54.940 --> 12:58.277
And he's wearing a clown mask.
Clowns are scary.

13:03.482 --> 13:05.951
- Ehhh.

13:06.018 --> 13:08.854
- Oooo, the bartender's here!

13:08.921 --> 13:10.456
- Hey, Schwoz.

13:10.523 --> 13:13.425
- Hello.

13:13.492 --> 13:17.897
- None of this is scary, dude!

13:17.963 --> 13:19.832
- And you have to make
a public speech!

13:22.101 --> 13:25.037
RAY: A speech
you're not prepared for!

13:27.039 --> 13:28.941
- I thrive under pressure, dude.

13:29.008 --> 13:31.777
- Yeah he's--
- Yeah, yeah.

13:31.844 --> 13:32.978
- Oh come on!

13:33.045 --> 13:34.613
How can you not be
scared by this?!

13:34.680 --> 13:36.815
That's a very scary reference
to a very scary movie!

13:36.882 --> 13:39.118
- He just doesn't get
why it's scary.

13:39.185 --> 13:41.153
- It's nuanced and artistic
and it's based on a book

13:41.220 --> 13:42.655
and the guy from Wings
was in it!

13:42.721 --> 13:43.989
- That's the version
you think of?

13:44.056 --> 13:46.592
- I told ya.
I can't be scared.

13:46.659 --> 13:47.826
Let me at them steaks!

13:47.893 --> 13:49.795
- Hold on there, handsome.
- What?

13:49.862 --> 13:52.731
- I was talking to Henry.
- Oh.

13:52.798 --> 13:55.634
- As Henry's best friend
and soul mate...

13:55.701 --> 13:56.902
- Wait what?
- Yeah, what?

13:56.969 --> 13:59.505
- I'm pretty sure I know
what scares him.

13:59.572 --> 14:03.842
- Oh I see... now you want
a shot at my steaks.

14:03.909 --> 14:05.644
- Yeah. I'm gonna win the bet,

14:05.711 --> 14:10.182
take all your steaks,
and then share them with you!

14:10.249 --> 14:12.351
- Okay, that defeats
the purpose of--

14:12.418 --> 14:15.988
- So flip down that visor
and be prepared to be scared!

14:18.490 --> 14:22.194
- Alright. This story takes
place up in Junk-N-Stuff...

14:22.261 --> 14:24.797
JASPER:
It was a day just like today.

14:24.863 --> 14:26.465
- Wait shouldn't it be
night right now?

14:26.532 --> 14:30.603
- Oh yeah, yeah. It's night,
that's way more scary.

14:30.669 --> 14:32.771
[ thunder ]

14:32.838 --> 14:35.007
You're halfway through weaving
a friendship bracelet

14:35.074 --> 14:37.042
for your ol' pal Jasper.

14:37.109 --> 14:41.547
JASPER: When suddenly,
Charlotte and I run in!

14:41.614 --> 14:43.816
- Hey what's up?
I'm almost done weaving your--

14:43.882 --> 14:45.651
- Zombies!!!

14:45.718 --> 14:49.188
[ Third Eye Blind -
"Semi-Charmed Life plays ]

14:56.128 --> 15:00.232
- You're right. Not yet.

15:00.299 --> 15:01.967
But soon...

15:08.774 --> 15:11.910
[ Jasper groans like a zombie ]

15:18.484 --> 15:20.252
- Do you have to
use the bathroom?

15:20.319 --> 15:22.421
- No I'm making zombie noises!

15:22.488 --> 15:26.592
- A zombie that has to
use the bathroom?

15:26.659 --> 15:28.861
- Why?
Would that be scarier?

15:28.927 --> 15:30.229
- Would somebody just please
scare Henry

15:30.296 --> 15:31.830
so we can win the bet
and get the steaks?!

15:31.897 --> 15:35.334
- That's what I'm doing!
- Are you?

15:35.401 --> 15:38.937
'Cuz I don't even see any
zombies in Junk-N-Stuff yet.

15:39.004 --> 15:40.906
I mean I'm looking
and I'm looking

15:40.973 --> 15:42.675
and I'm looking but--

15:42.741 --> 15:44.276
- Zombies!
- Okay.

15:46.512 --> 15:49.114
[ high-pitched classic horror
movie style scream ]

15:49.181 --> 15:51.050
- Please don't do that again.

15:51.116 --> 15:53.686
- It's Jasper's story.
I'm not in charge.

15:53.752 --> 15:55.954
- What do we do?
I'm so scared.

15:56.021 --> 15:59.358
And you should be, too!

15:59.425 --> 16:01.994
- The door's locked.
We're fine.

16:04.363 --> 16:07.733
No, no, no, I will not
be unlocking the door.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.468
[ zombies groan ]

16:09.535 --> 16:11.437
- Yeah, I know the sign says
we're open

16:11.503 --> 16:13.472
but it also says,
"Se habla Español"

16:13.539 --> 16:16.975
and none of us speak Spanish,
so it's always been wrong.

16:17.042 --> 16:20.279
[ zombies plead and groan ]

16:20.346 --> 16:24.049
- If I unlock the door are you
gonna eat my brains?

16:24.116 --> 16:27.820
[ zombies try to zombie-say
they won't ]

16:27.886 --> 16:30.155
- Are you zombie-lying?

16:30.222 --> 16:32.491
[ reluctantly zombie-admit
they are lying ]

16:32.558 --> 16:35.994
- And that's why I will not be
opening the door.

16:37.996 --> 16:42.334
- Oh no! That zombie
has a zombie key ring!

16:42.401 --> 16:44.503
[ high-pitched classic horror
movie style scream ]

16:44.570 --> 16:46.138
- Seriously?

16:46.205 --> 16:48.307
- This is what happens when guys
are in charge of stories.

16:48.374 --> 16:51.009
The women just stand there
and scream.

16:51.076 --> 16:52.811
- Oh no they unlocked
the door.

16:52.878 --> 16:55.114
I'm filled with fear!

16:55.180 --> 16:57.349
[ high-pitched, less
enthusiastic scream ]

16:58.150 --> 17:01.487
[ zombie groans ]

17:01.553 --> 17:04.790
- Why is my dad here?

17:04.857 --> 17:07.092
- I don't know but it's scary.

17:07.159 --> 17:08.493
- Is it? Cus why did we
go through

17:08.560 --> 17:10.128
that whole thing about
the door being locked

17:10.194 --> 17:11.829
if zombies were inside
the entire time?

17:11.896 --> 17:14.500
- There's no time to ask
reasonable questions because...

17:14.566 --> 17:17.368
I'm a zombie too!

17:20.271 --> 17:21.839
Oh, and so is Charlotte!

17:21.906 --> 17:25.077
- Really?

17:28.113 --> 17:30.482
[ zombies groan ]

17:30.549 --> 17:34.219
- Okay, okay, I get it.
Stop tickling me.

17:34.286 --> 17:36.555
Stop tickling me. I'm not gonna
be able to stop.

17:36.622 --> 17:39.224
I'm gonna pee my pants.
Stop guys, seriously.

17:39.291 --> 17:40.726
I'm not kidding. I'm not
kidding. I'm not kidding.

17:40.793 --> 17:42.494
I will pee my pants if you
don't stop tickling me.

17:42.561 --> 17:45.964
- He's not lying.
His urinol levels are rising!

17:47.399 --> 17:50.402
- The zombies are tickling you!
- No no no stop.

17:50.469 --> 17:51.904
- That's enough.
- It's not working.

17:51.970 --> 17:52.905
- I don't wanna see
my brother pee.

17:52.971 --> 17:54.540
- The zombies are doing this!

17:54.606 --> 17:56.074
- Stop, stop.

17:56.141 --> 17:58.076
- I thought we were friends.
- We are.

17:58.143 --> 17:59.878
- Alright that's enough.

17:59.945 --> 18:05.684
Now does anybody have any scary
stories that could scare Henry?

18:05.751 --> 18:09.755
- No they do not,
because I can't be scared.

18:09.822 --> 18:11.089
- I've got a scary story.

18:11.156 --> 18:12.524
- Fine.
- Oh great. Yes, yes, yes!

18:12.591 --> 18:14.560
Come on, come on, come on.
Do it, do it, do it.

18:14.626 --> 18:17.696
- It was a dark
and stormy night.

18:17.763 --> 18:20.432
Just like tonight, if tonight
were dark and stormy.

18:20.499 --> 18:22.868
- Right.

18:22.935 --> 18:24.603
CHARLOTTE: You're at your house.

18:24.670 --> 18:26.772
- Hey check it out.
Same couch.

18:26.839 --> 18:28.540
CHARLOTTE: Your dad and Piper
come home

18:28.607 --> 18:31.410
with a new doll
that Piper just bought.

18:31.477 --> 18:34.880
- We're home.
- With this doll I just bought.

18:34.947 --> 18:37.015
- Because it's an evil doll
that's gonna come to life

18:37.082 --> 18:39.184
and hurt me
while I'm sleeping?

18:39.251 --> 18:43.522
- Whaaaat?
- N-n-n-ooo...

18:43.589 --> 18:45.724
- Look at his face.
He's got murdery eyes.

18:45.791 --> 18:49.795
- Well that's just
too much mascara.

18:49.862 --> 18:51.363
- Face it.
The kid's onto me.

18:51.430 --> 18:53.131
This story's
not gonna scare him.

18:53.198 --> 18:56.034
Piper, just throw me
behind the couch.

18:56.101 --> 18:57.603
DOLL: Byyyyyyeeee!

18:59.137 --> 19:00.272
- Is that all you got?

19:00.339 --> 19:01.573
- Ooh ooh I got one.

19:01.640 --> 19:05.644
- Go, go. You got this.
- Yeah, yeah.

19:05.711 --> 19:07.045
- You're still at home.

19:07.112 --> 19:10.315
PIPER: But you're alone.

19:10.382 --> 19:13.252
- Oooo!
- With a baby.

19:13.318 --> 19:14.653
[ baby cries ]

19:14.720 --> 19:16.054
- Hey, this is the closest
any of these stories

19:16.121 --> 19:17.823
have gotten to being scary.

19:17.890 --> 19:19.625
- Alright!
- Go, go, go.

19:19.691 --> 19:22.561
- The phone rings!
You answer it...

19:22.628 --> 19:24.329
VOICE FROM PHONE:
Do you like scary movies?

19:24.396 --> 19:25.998
- I'll bet this call is coming
from inside the house.

19:26.064 --> 19:27.666
- Yeah, okay fine!

19:27.733 --> 19:29.835
But that's not all. Because
the person on the phone--

19:29.902 --> 19:31.937
- Is wearing a scary mask
from that painting

19:32.004 --> 19:33.539
and is holding a knife.

19:37.976 --> 19:39.845
DOLL: Ow!
- Dang it!

19:39.912 --> 19:41.914
- What?
- Come on!

19:41.980 --> 19:45.751
- Well, okay,
there's a full moon outside--

19:45.817 --> 19:49.087
- Werewolfs. Or vampires.
Whatever.

19:49.154 --> 19:50.756
- Ahhh!
- Ooooh!

19:53.525 --> 19:55.794
- Can I get out
of this story tank now?

19:55.861 --> 19:58.130
- No, no. Wait wait wait.

19:58.196 --> 20:00.198
[ groans in frustration ]

20:00.265 --> 20:03.802
- I have a story for you.

20:03.869 --> 20:06.338
It's very quick and very scary.

20:06.405 --> 20:08.040
- Okay. Let's hear it.

20:08.106 --> 20:11.043
- Once upon
fifteen minutes ago...

20:11.109 --> 20:14.713
{\an5}- Yeah.
- while Ray was telling you
his story...

20:14.780 --> 20:16.114
- Okay.

20:16.181 --> 20:21.119
- I infused the story tank
with butterfly DNA.

20:22.554 --> 20:25.891
- I'm sorry, what?
- Oh you didn't hear me?

20:25.958 --> 20:30.062
I said, I infused the story tank

20:30.128 --> 20:32.230
with butterfly DNA.

20:36.234 --> 20:39.471
- So what does that mean?

20:39.538 --> 20:42.641
- Fearitol levels rising.
- What?

20:42.708 --> 20:45.444
- And urinol.
- So much urinol...

20:47.546 --> 20:51.249
- Your story suit
is turning into a cocoon.

20:51.316 --> 20:53.085
[ Henry lets out a tiny shriek ]

20:53.151 --> 20:54.720
- Wait for it...wait for
it...wait for it.

20:54.786 --> 20:56.221
- Schwoz are we close?

20:56.288 --> 20:57.723
- So so-- what's gonna
happen to me, Schwoz?!

20:57.789 --> 21:00.525
- Well, you'll be in the cocoon
for about a month.

21:00.592 --> 21:01.927
- What?!
What about fighting crime?

21:01.994 --> 21:05.197
What about my parents?
What about school?

21:05.263 --> 21:07.265
- I don't know.

21:07.332 --> 21:09.568
I do know that when you emerge
from the cocoon,

21:09.635 --> 21:13.672
you will have a strong desire
to fly to Canada for the summer.

21:13.739 --> 21:15.107
- Noooo!

21:15.173 --> 21:16.108
- Oh oh!

21:16.174 --> 21:17.943
[ the monitor beeps ]

21:18.010 --> 21:20.612
- It's official.
Henry is scared!

21:20.679 --> 21:22.414
[ everyone except Henry cheers ]

21:22.481 --> 21:26.184
[ Third Eye Blind -
"Semi-Charmed Life plays ]

21:26.251 --> 21:28.286
- That was a great story,
Schwoz!

21:28.353 --> 21:29.855
- Thank you.
- This isn't a story!

21:29.921 --> 21:31.523
You actually did this to me!

21:31.590 --> 21:34.926
- Sometimes the scariest stories
are true.

21:34.993 --> 21:37.629
- Amen.
- Amen.

21:37.696 --> 21:39.464
- I don't want to be
a butterfly!

21:39.531 --> 21:42.567
I want something else!
- To get you through this?

21:42.634 --> 21:47.205
- Just undo this.
Control-Z, man! Control-Z!

21:47.272 --> 21:49.307
- Well it looks like
everything worked out.

21:49.374 --> 21:52.711
- Sure did, buddy.
- No it didn't!

21:52.778 --> 21:56.114
- Hey, hey, who wants to be
Kid Danger for the next month?!

21:56.181 --> 21:58.817
- Me, me!
- I do! I do!

21:58.884 --> 22:02.888
- I'm Kid Danger!
I wanna be Kid Danger!
